{"abstract":[{"text":"Gets a pointer to a region in ","type":"text"},{"code":"bytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"getRegion"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"elementSize"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"offset","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"nElements"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gconstpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gconstpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"?"}]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The region starts at ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"offset"},{"type":"text","text":" many bytes from the start of the data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and contains "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nElements"},{"text":" many elements of ","type":"text"},{"code":"elementSize","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" size."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nElements"},{"type":"text","text":" may be zero, but "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"elementSize"},{"text":" must always be non-zero.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"IDeally, "},{"code":"elementSize","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a static constant (eg: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sizeof"},{"text":" a struct).","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function does careful bounds checking (including checking for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"arithmetic overflows) and returns a non-"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NULL"},{"text":" pointer if the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified region lies entirely within the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"bytes"},{"type":"text","text":". If the region is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"in some way out of range, or if an overflow has occurred, then ","type":"text"},{"code":"NULL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is returned."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note: it is possible to have a valid zero-size region. In this case,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the returned pointer will be equal to the base pointer of the data of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"bytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", plus ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"offset"},{"type":"text","text":".  This will be non-"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NULL"},{"type":"text","text":" except for the case"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"where "},{"code":"bytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" itself was a zero-sized region.  Since it is unlikely"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that you will be using this function to check for a zero-sized region"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in a zero-sized "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"bytes"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NULL"},{"text":" effectively always means ‘error’.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"externalID":"s:4GLib13BytesProtocolPAAE9getRegion11elementSize6offset9nElementsSVSgSi_S2itF","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"GLib","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{